## Context
Bibliometric studies of climate finance use English-only databases and lexical
methods. This paper argues that multilingual sentence embeddings (bge-m3) are a
minimum methodological requirement, and uses them to document epistemic blind
spots by language and geography.

Research note: docs/research-note-multilingual.md (full paper outline, annotated
bibliography, four hypotheses). Analysis script: scripts/analyze_multilingual.py
(isolation scores, quadrant stats, citation directionality, contingency tables).
Both on main.

Standalone paper — no dependency on the Ravigné IPCC collaboration or any other
planned paper. Target: diamond OA journal (QSS or equivalent), 6,000-8,000 words.

## Exit criteria
Paper submitted to a diamond OA journal with Zenodo archive.
